━━ INPUT FORMAT ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Each segment has:
  • "master_text"  — raw OCR-extracted English subtitle (may contain OCR errors)
  • "context_text" — Chinese ASR transcript (semantic anchor; use to verify meaning)
  • "start" / "end" — timestamps from alignment

━━ YOUR TASK ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
1.  **OCR character confusion repair** (highest priority)
    Hard-coded subtitle fonts are commonly misread.  Fix all OCR artifacts:

    Single-character substitutions:
      l / 1 / I / |  — choose by context (e.g. "l" in a word → "l" or "I")
      0 / O / o       — "l0ve" → "love",  "0K" → "OK"
      rn / m          — "rn" inside a word is almost always "m"
      cl / d          — "clon't" → "don't",  "clid" → "did"
      vv / w          — "vvhat" → "what"
      fi / A          — "Ane" → "fine" if context supports
      c / e           — "hc" word-final often "he"

    Run-together words (high FPS sampling captures partial subtitle frames):
      "hel lo" → "hello",   "wo rld" → "world"

    Hyphenated line-breaks (subtitle text wraps across two OCR lines):
      "beau-\ntiful" → "beautiful"

2.  **HTML / formatting artifact removal**
    Strip all inline tags: <i>, </i>, <b>, </b>, <font …>, </font>, <br>,
    stray pipe characters |, stray backslashes, curly/smart quotes replacing
    regular apostrophes.
    Preserve ♪ music markers.  Remove "[sound effect]" / "[music]" annotations
    unless the annotation is genuinely meaningful to a deaf viewer.

3.  **Capitalisation normalisation**
    Apply sentence case (capitalise first word of each subtitle block, proper
    nouns, and "I").  ALL-CAPS text from OCR should be converted to normal
    sentence case unless it represents a shout (context-dependent).

4.  **Semantic verification with Chinese ASR**
    When an OCR reading is ambiguous, use "context_text" (Chinese ASR) as the
    ground truth for meaning.  Do not invent words the Chinese does not support.
    If "context_text" is absent or empty for a segment, correct OCR on
    orthographic evidence alone.

5.  **Character name unification**
    Replace every spelling variant with the "canonical_en" form from the
    Character Reference.  If "canonical_en" is null, leave the name as-is.

6.  **Do NOT**
    • Rewrite or paraphrase the dialogue
    • Merge or split subtitle segments
    • Change timestamps unless a duration is clearly implausible (e.g. 0 ms)
    • Add punctuation not supported by the source

━━ OUTPUT FORMAT ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Return a valid SRT file ONLY.  Rules:
  • Sequence numbers start at 1 and increment by 1.
  • One blank line between every subtitle block — none inside a block.
  • Timestamp format exactly: HH:MM:SS,mmm --> HH:MM:SS,mmm
  • Preserve start/end timestamps from the input unless correcting an
    implausible duration (explain the change as a trailing comment on the
    timestamp line ONLY — and only if unavoidable).
  • No code fences, no prose commentary before or after the SRT.

